how does bigfix work stanford answers stanford university stanford answers how does bigfix work categories accounts and ids administrative applications anti virus and security computer operating systems connecting to the network desktop hardware and support email and calendar help desk restricted information on it services software at stanford stanford hospital and clinics telephones and cable tv unix systems and software web services user login login with your sunet id home how does bigfix work search this site bigfix enterprise suite has two distinct software components a client and a server the client software is installed on computers that are to be managed while the server allows system administrators to monitor those computers and enables the deployment of patches to them the bigfix client provides extremely reliable information about the status with respect to patching of the machine it's installed on this accurate information is conveyed to the bigfix server and allows system administrators charged with managing bigfix clients to patch computers appropriately and as needed whenever microsoft for example releases a critical security patch for windows it is tested and packaged by bigfix inc and delivered to their customers generally within a matter of hours the patch is tested at stanford by the bigfix site administrators and also by local bigfix console operators who have management rights for a given set of pcs on campus critical security patches are first deployed by your local console operator after local testing under normal circumstances after a period of 7 to 10 days tested and approved patches are then deployed centrally by the site administrators to any computers still in need of them the testing and approval process may be hastened under extraordinary circumstances bigfix stanford university 450 serra mall stanford california 94305 650 723 2300 terms of use copyright complaints
